@NODE intro "Introduction"

NetMenu is a small program designed to launch your Internet software from
a small and simple interface, much like the ones that some internet
providers supply. NetMenu may be better than some of these because:

   * Provides control over s/w via ARexx scripts
   * Plays a little sample when you launch each program :)
   * Font sensitive, re-sizeable GUI
   * Simplistic GUI means very easy to use
   * Very configurable
   * Source code included so it can be totally customised
   
@ENDNODE

